            <title>[LU-13769] osd_dir_it_key and osd_index_it_key feed zap_cursor_retrieve return to ERR_PTR</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13769</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;it looks like both do&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
       &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ((rc = -zap_cursor_retrieve(it-&amp;gt;ozi_zc, za)))
                RETURN(ERR_PTR(rc));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But in fact it could return a wildly positive value that would break ERR_PTR as advised by smatch?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
